--- SCENARIO: commands are answered in the topic they came from ---
# A Telegram forum group is one chat split into several topics (sub-channels) that share a
# chat id but differ by message_thread_id. The bot used to drop every reply into the General
# topic; it must instead answer in whichever topic the command arrived in. Here three
# conversations run in parallel — two named topics plus General — and each reply must land in
# its own topic, never leaking into another.

--- TOPIC (drafting) ---
alice: /lobby
ambotorix: Lobby created by alice

--- TOPIC (chatter) ---
bob: /time
ambotorix: *Current time*

--- TOPIC (drafting) ---
bob: /register
ambotorix: Player bob added to lobby*        # * = the "open a private chat" DM warning

--- CHAT ---                                  # the General topic (no message_thread_id)
alice: /help
ambotorix: *General:*

# Each topic saw only its own replies — nothing crossed over.
--- TOPIC (chatter) ---
ambotorix:

--- TOPIC (drafting) ---
ambotorix:

--- CHAT ---
ambotorix:
